34MultiFormatReader::MultiFormatReader(const DecodeHints& hints)
35{
36 bool tryHarder = hints.tryHarder();
37 if (!hints.hasNoFormat()) {
38 bool addOneDReader =
39 hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::UPC_A) ||
40 hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::UPC_E) ||
41 hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::EAN_13) ||
42 hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::EAN_8) ||
43 hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::CODABAR) ||
44 hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::CODE_39) ||
45 hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::CODE_93) ||
46 hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::CODE_128) ||
47 hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::ITF) ||
48 hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::RSS_14) ||
49 hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::RSS_EXPANDED);
50
51 // Put 1D readers upfront in "normal" mode
52 if (addOneDReader && !tryHarder) {
53 _readers.emplace_back(new OneD::Reader(hints));
54 }
55 if (hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::QR_CODE)) {
56 _readers.emplace_back(new QRCode::Reader(hints));
57 }
58 if (hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::DATA_MATRIX)) {
59 _readers.emplace_back(new DataMatrix::Reader(hints));
60 }
61 if (hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::AZTEC)) {
62 _readers.emplace_back(new Aztec::Reader());
63 }
64 if (hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::PDF_417)) {
65 _readers.emplace_back(new Pdf417::Reader());
66 }
67 if (hints.hasFormat(BarcodeFormat::MAXICODE)) {
68 _readers.emplace_back(new MaxiCode::Reader(hints));
69 }
70 // At end in "try harder" mode
71 if (addOneDReader && tryHarder) {
72 _readers.emplace_back(new OneD::Reader(hints));
73 }
74 }
75
76 if (_readers.empty()) {
77 if (!tryHarder) {
78 _readers.emplace_back(new OneD::Reader(hints));
79 }
80 _readers.emplace_back(new QRCode::Reader(hints));
81 _readers.emplace_back(new DataMatrix::Reader(hints));
82 _readers.emplace_back(new Aztec::Reader());
83 _readers.emplace_back(new Pdf417::Reader());
84 _readers.emplace_back(new MaxiCode::Reader(hints));
85 if (tryHarder) {
86 _readers.emplace_back(new OneD::Reader(hints));
87 }
88 }
89}
90
91MultiFormatReader::~MultiFormatReader() = default;
92
93Result
94MultiFormatReader::read(const BinaryBitmap& image) const
95{
96 // If we have only one reader in our list, just return whatever that decoded.
97 // This preserves information (e.g. ChecksumError) instead of just returning 'NotFound'.
98 if (_readers.size() == 1)
99 return _readers.front()->decode(image);
100
101 for (const auto& reader : _readers) {
102 Result r = reader->decode(image);
103 if (r.isValid())
104 return r;
105 }
106 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
107}
